M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 weakly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 59-62
) 0.41-0.47 mm long, symmetrical, moderately sclerotized. Median lobe with very short, inflexed apical process and large, bulbous articular process. Parameres large, bearing ventral membranous lobes, strongly narrowed toward tip in dorsal view. Internal sac with tip of flagellum expanded.
